<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n Christ by the holy Ghost, &amp; y^<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> most blessed &amp; honorable Sacramente of Baptisme, he streyght falleth in ha~d with vs, labouryng by one meanes or other vtterly to allure &amp; entise vs from our profession, as we may se in our sauyour &amp; <HI>LORDE</HI> Iesus Christ,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mat. iiii. Mar i. Luke, iiii&punc;</NOTE> whome after his Baptisme Satan dyd not feare to assayle and to te~pte vnto muche absurditie and wicked|nes. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f the sonne of God were not free from his crafte, subtilite &amp; gyle, howe shall we than miserable creatu+res eschewe his tyranny, whiche are redy to faull at euery houre, excepte we watche and praye. Our stryfe is not,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ephe. vi.</NOTE> sayth S. Paule, agaynst bloud &amp; flesshe, but agaynst rulers, against the powers, agaynste the Lordes of the world, I mene, the gouernours of y^e darkenes of this world, agaynst spirituall subtilities in heaue~ly thi|ges. Therfore sayeth S. Peter:<NOTE PLACE="marg">i. Pet. v.</NOTE> Be ye sober and watche, for your aduer+sary
